<br>
I was buffed to 4k HP and runed to start.<br>
<br>
I cast high taunt spells on Maestro and pulled him to the corner where I continued to use taunt spells through the entire fight.<br>
<br>
Cleric was using only CH on me and smaller heals on people damaged by his AE lifetap.<br>
<br>
There we no deaths and Maestro never turned away from me.<br>
<br>
A Very Unpleasant Hand went differently however.  Same tactic, but I accidently switched targets during the fight and didn't notice, so my taunt spells weren't hitting.<br>
<br>
About the time my cleric got eaten I switched back to hand and regained aggro...  shouted for healers to watch my health, but nobody was casting CH.  Small heals were unable to keep me standing and after death pact saved me from the first death, I died a second time.  Once I fell a handful more fell before finally finishing the hand.<br>
<br>
For what it's worth, none of my spells ever stuck to the Maestro, but resisted spells still taunt for full.<br>
<br>
It is almost impossible for a cleric to take aggro away from an SK (or other class with fast, high taunt spells).  Even fighting Faydedar, neither of my clerics were aggroed until after I died.  They were chain casting complete heals about 6-8 seconds apart.  They both died OOM, after I fell. <p>Krazaak Crushbone<BR>
54th Troll Reaver [Shadow Knight]<BR>
