Myriah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umenniantheelder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mennian The Elder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/8/01 3:02:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=188.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Cleric Healing</span><hr size=1> It has been my experience that uber mobs are only defeated if taken down as quickly as possible.  Basically like gambling, the longer the it goes on, the less the likelihood of winning.  This is why most clerics including myself rarely if ever use Complete Heal when fighting an uber mob unless we have a group comprised solely of level 55 plus tanks. <br>
<br>
The goal as a cleric when fighting an uber mob isn't to be totally mana efficient or keep every single person in the group alive (sorry tanks).  The goal is to keep as many in your party alive for as long as possible so the greatest amount of damage can be done against the mob.  Losing one tank after the first couple minutes of battle isn't gonna be a backbreaker.  Complete heal is simply too risky to use in my opinion in achieving the goal of keeping everyone alive for as long as possible.  If the mob is on one tank the whole time that is one thing, but most uber mobs use AoE damage and don't stay on one target.  Spending ten seconds to cast CH on a tank if you have casters in a group is simply not worth the risk.  The mana you might save by using CH will not make the difference.  Celestial healing, divine light, and remedy have much lower cast times, and are considerably easier to use.<br>
<br>
Any caster (doesn't need to be a cleric) can tell you how extremely important a low cast time is.  The chances that CH will be interupted or specialization won't &quot;kick in&quot; weigh too heavily against its use on uber mobs.  Especially against the Maestro this last time when additional add mobs jumped in increasing the likelihood of getting interupted.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I am not saying CH is worthless against uber mobs.  I always have it memmed (unless I don't have tanks in the group) and will use it if I feel there isn't a risk to the other tanks and casters in my group.<br>
<br>
There is one last problem with casting CH in fights like these.  Typically against uber mobs you have upwards of 30 people all running around in a small area.  What does that translate to?  How about LAG.  Maybe tanks aren't especially concerned or bothered by it, but casters, especially clerics, have enormous problems with timing of spells when suffering lag. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umenniantheelder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mennian The Elder</A> at: 5/8/01 3:20:47 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF00>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bsaryrnguildallianceboard>saryrnguildallianceboard</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1>General Discussion</a> <font color=#FFFF00> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://www.qksrv.net/click-553273-1925262" target="_blank" >
